Binary & Single Star Tables
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The binary and single star tables include information on the star's spectral
 type, cluster distances, absolute J, H & K magnitudes, delta J, H & K,
 angular seperations, and primary angles.
 These were calculated using the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

cent_aper_final.py
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 program in the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Photometry
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 folder.
 Isochrone reduced masses are also displayed on the spreadsheet.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Cluster Tables
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The cluster tables in the spreadsheet display the distances and ages for
 each cluster.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Isochrones for Clusters
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For mass ratios below 0.5, we used the NextGen isochrone.
 Additionally, we examined the isochrone mass vs luminosity, effective temperatu
re, and age, age vs apparent magnitude, and the mass histogram for each
 cluster (isochron_age.py).
\end_layout

